Pancreatitis with normal serum amylase associated with sodium valproate: a case report. The patient was a 1-year-old infant with severe postencephalitis syndrome. Diarrhea and elevation of the pancreatic enzymes, except for serum amylase (elastase 1 > 1, 5000 ng/dl (100-400) lipase, 885 IU/I/37 degrees C (10-48)